<h2 class="page-title span-24">Case Study: Nissan Europe</h2>

<div class="header span-24">
  <div class="span-19 last">
    <h1>
      <span class="dark-green">Nissan Europe’s smaller divisions needed adaptability</span><br />
      on a fixed budget and a tight timeline.
    </h1>
    <img src="http://static.gossamer-threads.com/r3/images/logos/logo-nissan-120x90.png" width="120" height="90" alt="Nissan logo" />
  </div>
</div><!-- end .header -->

<div class="span-15 append-1 content-text"><!-- main-col -->
  <h2>Challenge</h2>
  <p>
    Nissan needed a set of flexible, dynamic websites that could be updated by
    local representatives in smaller European markets in order to minimize
    expenses and overhead. Although they didn’t have the marketing budgets
    found in larger markets (like Germany or the UK), smaller divisions like
    Nissan Malta, Nissan Iceland, and Nissan Cyprus still needed to easily
    create, manage, and maintain up-to-date information on vehicles and
    pricing.
  </p>

  <h2>Solution</h2>
  <p>
    Gossamer Threads utilized its proprietary database management application
    <a href="/products/gossamer-links/">Gossamer Links</a> —along with some
    custom modifications— to ease workflow and provide a user-friendly experience for
    those working in dealerships. To accomplish this, a consistent interface was used in both website's front-end and the back-end administrative tools. Additionally, a set of checks and balances was established to simplify the
    administration of content while minimizing user error. To achieve more on
    a limited budget, Nissan’s larger market divisions shared existing
    assets in order to minimize additional creative costs.
  </p>

  <h2>Results</h2>
  <p>
    With an eye to the tight timelines requested by Nissan Europe, Gossamer
    implemented a language-independent solution which allows Nissan Europe, in
    tandem with Gossamer's developers, to deploy new microsites in a matter of
    weeks rather than months. Combined with hosting in Gossamer Threads'
    European data centre, Nissan Europe's small market outlets now have the
    ability to manage their websites readily (by those with non-technical
    expertise) while conforming to Nissan's global brand standards.
  </p>

  <p class="more"><a href="/products/gossamer-links/">More about Gossamer Links&nbsp;<span>&raquo;</span></a></p>

  <h2>Other Case Studies</h2>
  <p>
    <a href="/results/enterprise/aeroplan.html"><img src="http://static.gossamer-threads.com/r3/images/logos/logo-aeroplan-110x90.png" width="110" height="90" alt="Aeroplan" /></a>
    <a href="/results/enterprise/department-of-defense.html"><img src="http://static.gossamer-threads.com/r3/images/logos/logo-usdod-110x90.png" width="110" height="90" alt="Department of Defense" /></a>
  </p>

</div><!-- end main-col -->

<div class="span-5 append-3 last"><!-- inner-right-col -->
  <p class="huge-text">1 wk</p>
  <p>
    From content collation to site launch, each Nissan minisite has a one week
    turnaround.
  </p>
  <hr />

  <h2>They said</h2>
  <blockquote>
    <p>
      “Having worked on several projects now with Gossamer Threads, Nissan
      is very pleased with the quality, attention to detail and speed of the
      solutions and outcomes of the projects. Having Gossamer on hand
      essentially 24-7 is also of a huge benefit. For a European operation,
      having an agency based in Canada is a great help to us as it means we can
      brief in requests last thing in the evening, and they are ready for sign
      off by the time we start our next working day.“
    </p>
    <div class="pointer"></div>
  </blockquote>
  <p>
    <em>
      – Gareth Dunsmore, Interactive Marketing<br />
      - Nissan Europe
    </em>
  </p>
  <hr />

